instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "Fidelity concerns focus on reducing backlash and positional uncertainty in the mechanical drive, thereby improving the robot control’s accuracy. Validation is performed by comparing simulated data against measured data streams; deviations are identified as a measure of model validity. Failure to achieve acceptable alignment between simulation and observation triggers corrective model adjustments, and continuous monitoring ensures that model fidelity remains within defined tolerances."
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "The system adopts a set of modeling standards to ensure consistency and interoperability. It uses SysML and UML, both defined by the Object Management Group (OMG), for structural and behavioral modeling. Component‑connector interactions are modeled with Architecture Description Languages (ADLs) such as ACME, AADL, and MontiArc, the latter providing an automaton extension for state‑based behavior. Behavioral sequencing is further supported by SysML v1.7 state machine diagrams and MontiArc Automaton formulations. For simulation and validation, MathWorks Simulink is integrated to execute the models. No explicit mention of industry certification programs, compliance frameworks, or additional interoperability standards is provided in the document."
]
